sbml2modelica.sbmlabstraction

Class ReactionAbstractionManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • sbml2modelica.sbmlabstraction.ReactionAbstractionManager

  • public class ReactionAbstractionManager
extends java.lang.Object
    A ReactionAbstractionManager provides functionalities for generation of AbstractReactions, and their related AbstractSpeciesReferences, in an AbstractModel from the informations provided by a SBML Model.
    The ReactionAbstractionManager works under the assumption that the SBML Model has been pre-processed with a ModelPreprocessingManager.
    Author:
    Maggioli Filippo

    • Method Detail

      • generateReactant

        private AbstractSpeciesReference generateReactant(AbstractReaction ar,
                                                  org.sbml.jsbml.SpeciesReference sr)
                                           throws NullSpeciesException
        This method generates the AbstractSpeciesReference, stoichiometry of a reactant in the AbstractReaction, that represents the given SBML SpeciesReference.
        After the call of this method, the generated AbstractSpeciesReference only represents informations about the identifier, the name, the AbstractReaction in which it is located and the AbstractSpecies that it refers.
        Note that if there is no AbstractSpecies in the AbstractModel that represents the SBML Species referred by the given SBML SpeciesReference.
        Parameters:
        ar - The AbstractReaction in which the AbstractSpeciesReference is defined.
        sr - The SBML SpeciesReference that contains the informations.
        Returns:
        The AbstractSpeciesReference that represents the given SBML SpeciesReference.
        Throws:
        NullSpeciesException - When there is no AbstractSpecies in the AbstractModel with the same identifier as that of the SBML Species referred by the given SBML SpeciesReference.

      • generateLocalParameter

        private AbstractLocalParameter generateLocalParameter(AbstractReaction ar,
                                                      org.sbml.jsbml.LocalParameter p)
        This method generates an AbstractLocalParameter, in the given AbstractReaction, that represents the given SBML Parameter.
        Note that differently from the other generation methods in the AbstractionManagers, this method generates an AbstractLocalParameter that completely represents its SBML counterpart.
        Parameters:
        ar - The AbstractReaction in which the AbstractLocalParameter must be generated.
        p - The SBML Parameter that contains the informations.
        Returns:
        The AbstractLocalParameter that represents the given SBML Parameter.

      • generateReaction

        private AbstractReaction generateReaction(org.sbml.jsbml.Reaction r)
        This method generates the AbstractReaction, in the AbstractModel, that represents the given SBML Reaction.
        The method also generates all the AbstractSpeciesReferences and the AbstractLocalParameters associated with the AbstractReaction.
        Note that after the call to this method the generated AbstractReaction and the AbstractSpeciesReferences associated with it only represents generic informations and nothing about values.
        Parameters:
        r - The SBML Reaction that contains the informations.
        Returns:
        The AbstractReaction that represents the SBML Reaction.

      • generateReactions

        void generateReactions()
        This method generates all the AbstractReactions in the AbstractModel that represent the SBML Reactions in the SBML Model.
        After the call to this method, the AbstractReactions and their associated AbstractSpeciesReferences only contains informations not concerning values. Differently, the AbstractLocalParameters are completely defined.

      • computeSpeciesReferenceValue

        private void computeSpeciesReferenceValue(AbstractSpeciesReference asr,
                                          org.sbml.jsbml.SpeciesReference sr)
        This method computes an AbstractValue that represents the value of the given SBML SpeciesReference in the SBML Model and associates that AbstractValue with the given AbstractSpeciesReference.
        Parameters:
        sr - A SBML SpeciesReference in the SBML Model.
        asr - An AbstractSpeciesReference in the AbstractModel that represents the given SBML SpeciesReference.
